From 67215aa9d5d931c2758933faad7e1e0ca7b06c5c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Matei Dobrescu <contact@md0.ro>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 01:33:00 +0300
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] Miyoo Mini (Allium CFW) port integration hooks (mmx_miyoo
 module)

Wires the self-contained mmx_miyoo module (mmx_miyoo.c/h/cmake, shipped
separately) into the engine, enabled by -DALIS_MIYOO_ALLIUM=ON:

- CMakeLists: ALIS_MIYOO_ALLIUM option; on Miyoo include src/mmx_miyoo.cmake
  (static SDL2 with OSS audio, no video/joystick backends) instead of
  find_package(SDL2), build src/mmx_miyoo.c, skip the standalone emu2149
  lib (it overrides CMAKE_C_FLAGS and breaks cross builds; alis compiles
  emu2149.c directly)
- sys.c: route SDL_GetKeyboardState/SDL_GetModState to the evdev-fed shim
  (no SDL video driver on device means SDL's own state never updates);
  OR the Miyoo button bits into sys_joy_compose
- sys_sdl2.c: init without video/joystick and with non-fatal audio; poll
  evdev buttons each cycle; present frames via /dev/fb0 instead of the
  SDL renderer; no mouse cursor; audio open failure continues muted
  (sound needs Allium's libpadsp.so OSS shim, see launch.sh)

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
